fields.Title: ICE / ACELE CHURCH STUFF
fields.Description: this is where "the drug lab plan conclusion", "what did you see in the church" and "what's your plan for the church" branches are located

fields.Title: Acele: ""May I ask, what did you tell them?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "May I ask, what did you tell them?"

fields.Title: You: ""Strange things happen.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Strange things happen."

fields.Title: Drama: "C'mon. She obviously could. She alr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: C'mon. She obviously could. She already went into detail.

fields.Title: Acele: ""Thank you," the young woman says b..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Thank you," the young woman says blithely. "I'll get them under wraps, I promise."

fields.Title: Acele: ""Oh, that... you're not gonna belie..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh, that... you're not gonna believe me. There's no point in me telling you."

fields.Title: You: ""That's not especially frightening.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's not especially frightening."

fields.Title: Acele: ""They're inside that thing there."..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "They're inside that thing there." She points to the tent. "Would be cool if you did... Was there something else?"

fields.Title: Acele: ""Not really, no.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Not really, no."

fields.Title: Acele: ""Synthesizers and tape consoles, mi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Synthesizers and tape consoles, microcomputers too. Anything that uses electricity, but isn't guitars... also found sounds. Stuff like that."

fields.Title: Acele: ""She was dressed like someone who's..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "She was dressed like someone who's being raised by their grandmother, you know. Strange old clothes. Had this absent expression, didn't say anything, just stood still."

fields.Title: You: ""I already spoke with them and agre..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I already spoke with them and agreed to help."
fields.Alternate1: "I already spoke with them and we've agreed to help."

fields.Title: You: "(Nod.) "I saw him. I saw the crab-m..."
fields.Dialogue Text: (Nod.) "I saw him. I saw the crab-man."

fields.Title: You: ""I did see them both, yes.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I did see them both, yes."

fields.Title: You: ""I prefer not to share this informa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I prefer not to share this information with you."

fields.Title: Acele: ""I did and I'm sorry." She doesn't..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I did and I'm sorry." She doesn't appear surprised. "For what it's worth... which isn't much."
fields.Alternate1: "I did and I'm sorry. For what it's worth... which isn't much."

fields.Title: You: ""I needed some reál, Kim. It's a ha..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I needed some reál, Kim. It's a hard knock life."

fields.Title: You: ""Go on.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Go on."

fields.Title: Acele: ""I don't blame you. I mean, I would..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't blame you. I mean, I wouldn't believe me either. I'm surprised Noid did. Andre I expected, but Noid..." She shakes her head.

fields.Title: Shivers: "The floorboards are twisting and th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The floorboards are twisting and the shooting beams are slowly cracking like bones. Far east of the golden Delta, beyond the industrial port, there is a black patch of unlit coast with the smallest creatures on the ice...

fields.Title: Shivers: "Not in a million years."
fields.Dialogue Text: Not in a million years.

fields.Title: You: "(Show her the sticker on your ledge..."
fields.Dialogue Text: (Show her the sticker on your ledger.) "So, this isn't yours?"

fields.Title: You: ""Wait, is this *Noid* a friend of y..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wait, is this *Noid* a friend of yours?"

fields.Title: Acele: ""C'mon, man. Don't mess around..."..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "C'mon, man. Don't mess around..." She hesitates.

fields.Title: Acele: ""You *saw* him?!" She leans closer...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You *saw* him?!" She leans closer. "Does it mean that you went *in* there? Did you see the other spooker, the one in grandma's clothes?"

fields.Title: Acele: ""Oh. Okay." She sits back on the bl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh. Okay." She sits back on the blanket, ears red from cold. "What about Andre? You should go talk to Andre if you don't want to talk to me."

fields.Title: You: ""Instead you opted to omit the trut..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Instead you opted to omit the truth. It's the same thing."

fields.Title: Acele: ""Okey dokey then.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okey dokey then."

fields.Title: You: ""I took a cut of the action. I'm co..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I took a cut of the action. I'm corrupt to the marrow, you see."
fields.Alternate1: (Tell the truth.) "I took a cut of the action. I'm corrupt to the marrow, you see."

fields.Title: You: ""You know a good doughnut joint?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "You know a good doughnut joint?"

fields.Title: You: ""You were wrong. I do believe you.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "You were wrong. I do believe you."

fields.Title: Acele: ""*Why?*" She raises a brow."
fields.Dialogue Text: "*Why?*" She raises a brow.

fields.Title: You: ""Did you put the padlock on the chu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Did you put the padlock on the church door?"

fields.Title: Acele: ""Yes, a 'banger', as in a Mesque ga..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, a 'banger', as in a Mesque gang-member. I know what it sounds like, but that's what I saw."

fields.Title: You: ""Should've tried harder. Misleading..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Should've tried harder. Misleading a cop is no joke."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Good call, detective," he says, st..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good call, detective," he says, still looking at the ocean. "You can lose your mind trying to mediate everything these delinquents come up with. Fate will take care of it for us."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""No. Conduct your side-interview an..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No. Conduct your side-interview and let's move on to the case at hand."

fields.Title: Shivers: "There will never be a club for anod..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There will never be a club for anodic music here.

fields.Title: Acele: ""Okay, well..." She hesitates. "May..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, well..." She hesitates. "Maybe you could *talk* to Andre and the guys? Because there are some strange things going on in that church... if you're police you should look into it, right?"

fields.Title: Acele: ""He looked like a banger, okay? He..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "He looked like a banger, okay? He was all muscular and stuff. Had a mesh tanktop. I know it sounds ridiculous, but that only made it scarier, in a way..."

fields.Title: You: ""You were right. I don't believe yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You were right. I don't believe you."
fields.Alternate1: "A gangster crab-man... Yeah, I don't believe you."

fields.Title: Acele: ""It's supposed to become, like, a c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's supposed to become, like, a club. For *anodic dance music*. Like that new style of synthesizer stuff they play at The Paliseum."

fields.Title: You: ""No?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "No?"

fields.Title: Jump to: [Acele: ""What do you need to know?""]
Acele: ""Hey, remember how earlier I said I..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hey, remember how earlier I said I didn't *need* your help?"

fields.Title: You: ""Once I cracked their play I didn't..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Once I cracked their play I didn't really care. I'm not an arbiter. You're someone else's problem."

fields.Title: Acele: ""He stopped right before he got to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "He stopped right before he got to the floor, then just hung there like that, looking at me. Right at me. I fucking turned around and walked out. End of story."

fields.Title: Acele: ""We won't be anyone's problem. I'll..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We won't be anyone's problem. I'll get them under wraps, I promise."

fields.Title: Acele: ""I guess so." She hesitates. "Anywa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I guess so." She hesitates. "Anyway -- what else?"

fields.Title: Acele: ""Doesn't hurt to ask, I guess..." S..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Doesn't hurt to ask, I guess..." She shrugs.

fields.Title: You: ""I'll talk to them.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'll talk to them."

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "She's trying to get out of a direct..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She's trying to get out of a direct lie with semantic tricks. *She personally* didn't put the padlock on the door.

fields.Title: Acele: ""Yes, a 'banger', as in a Mesque ga..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, a 'banger', as in a Mesque gang-member. I know what it sounds like, but that's what I saw."

fields.Title: You: ""Do what you will with your dance c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Do what you will with your dance club plans... just no drug labs, please."

fields.Title: Acele: ""You don't get to choose your posse..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You don't get to choose your posse, they choose you. Mine are idiots, but they're mine. I tried to talk Andre out of it, I even tried not to lie to you..."

fields.Title: You: ""I don't care, I'm *loco*. I just w..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't care, I'm *loco*. I just wanted you to know that I know about the plan."

fields.Title: Acele: ""Oh!" She almost smiles, but then d..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh!" She almost smiles, but then decides not to. There's a moment of silence.

fields.Title: You: ""What is *anodic dance music*?"
fields.Dialogue Text: "What is *anodic dance music*?
fields.Alternate1: "Anodic music?! *Now* I'm gonna find out what it is! What is it?"

fields.Title: You: ""I've got enough on my plate as it..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I've got enough on my plate as it is."
fields.Alternate1: "Yeah, I've spoken with them. No way in hell am I getting involved in this."

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "You see clear, beautiful, violent f..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You see clear, beautiful, violent flashes of light. Light cutting through a smoke-filled darkness. That is what the future will look like -- if it ever comes.

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "This is an evolutionary step up fro..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is an evolutionary step up from amplified instruments, which in turn are a step up from acoustic instruments. What comes after it, you wonder: a black-tinted nothingness, or something finer?

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""This is why I didn't go into the t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This is why I didn't go into the tent." The lieutenant looks at the ocean, squinting his eyes. "Typical delinquency."

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "Indeed. She merely tried to omit th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Indeed. She merely tried to omit the truth instead.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Please officer, just finish your s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Please officer, just finish your side-interview. We need to move on to the case at hand."

fields.Title: Drama: "Your words flow sincere."
fields.Dialogue Text: Your words flow sincere.

fields.Title: Acele: ""It was too dark." She shakes her h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It was too dark." She shakes her head. "I couldn't tell exactly."

fields.Title: You: "(Show her the sticker in your ledge..."
fields.Dialogue Text: (Show her the sticker in your ledger.) "So, this isn't yours?"

fields.Title: Acele: ""Thank you." The young woman nods...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Thank you." The young woman nods. "I'll get them under wraps, I promise."

fields.Title: You: ""What did this 'crab-man' look like?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What did this 'crab-man' look like?"

fields.Title: You: ""Got it. Now about the church...""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Got it. Now about the church..."

fields.Title: Acele: ""Hey..." Her black eyes widen. "You..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hey..." Her black eyes widen. "You're a cop..."
fields.Alternate1: "Hey..." Her black eyes widen. "You two are cops..."

fields.Title: You: "(Forgo celebrating your triumph.) "..."
fields.Dialogue Text: (Forgo celebrating your triumph.) "Now about the church..."

fields.Title: Half Light: "Should you? *Weirdos* sounds bad so..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Should you? *Weirdos* sounds bad somehow.

fields.Title: You: ""No, just the crab-man.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "No, just the crab-man."

fields.Title: You: ""That I'm going to decide after I'v..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That I'm going to decide after I've looked into the church situation."

fields.Title: Acele: ""You don't get to choose your posse..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You don't get to choose your posse, they choose you. Mine are idiots, but they're mine. I tried to talk Andre out of it..."

fields.Title: Acele: ""Okay, but I still regret it. I sho..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, but I still regret it. I should have been able to control them. And I will in the future. I promise."

fields.Title: Acele: ""I know. But I knew you'd see throu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I know. But I knew you'd see through their plan too. I'm not an idiot. I should have been able to control them. I will in the future. I promise."

fields.Title: You: "Try to lie about your actions in fr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Try to lie about your actions in front of the lieutenant.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""As good a call as any..." the lieu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "As good a call as any..." the lieutenant says, still looking at the ocean. "Better not to have made one at all though. You'll lose your mind trying to mediate everything these delinquents come up with."

fields.Title: Acele: ""And then, you know, right behind h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "And then, you know, right behind her a man *crawled down the wall*. Upside down, like a crab. Down the church wall. I think the woman didn't even know he was there, he was completely silent..."

fields.Title: Acele: ""Okay then," she nods. "They certai..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay then," she nods. "They certainly do around me."

fields.Title: You: ""So you want to turn the church int..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "So you want to turn the church into a club?"

fields.Title: Acele: ""To keep more weirdos from getting..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "To keep more weirdos from getting in. Fucking Martinaise... I'm sorry." She rattles her teeth. "It's got the worst weirdos. If you get around to it, ask Andre about them, he'll tell you."

fields.Title: You: ""I don't know where you got that id..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't know where you got that idea."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Like a *crab*, you say?" The lieut..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Like a *crab*, you say?" The lieutenant nods. His face is stone.

fields.Title: Empathy: "She seems incredibly controlled all..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She seems incredibly controlled all of a sudden. Her fists are clenched and she looks straight ahead. She's keeping herself together with all her might, rippling on the inside.

fields.Title: You: "(Whisper.) "It's all a ruse. I'm ac..."
fields.Dialogue Text: (Whisper.) "It's all a ruse. I'm actually super deep under cover, blurring the lines between reality and make-believe."

fields.Title: You: ""Seems too ludicrous for a lie.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Seems too ludicrous for a lie."

fields.Title: Acele: ""Okay," she nods. "I went in and sa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay," she nods. "I went in and saw a woman next to one of those machines there. Noid calls it a *mainframe*..."

fields.Title: You: ""Enough about the church then. I ha..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Enough about the church then. I had a another question." (Conclude.)

fields.Title: Acele: ""No.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "No."

fields.Title: Acele: ""Hey... don't get me wrong. But you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hey... don't get me wrong. But you're a *cop*, right..."
fields.Alternate1: "Hey... don't get me wrong, but you're *cops*, right..."

fields.Title: Drama: "Thine lies, they sing too transpare..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Thine lies, they sing too transparent.

fields.Title: Acele: ""It's Noid's padlock, for keeping c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's Noid's padlock, for keeping creeps and weirdos out. You should probably talk to him about it."

fields.Title: Acele: ""Soooo...?" The young woman looks a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Soooo...?" The young woman looks at you, then the lieutenant, then you again. Then at the shore. She seems uncomfortable.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Okay. Now conduct your side-interv..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay. Now conduct your side-interview and let's move on to the case at hand."

fields.Title: You: ""You're right. Let me ask you about..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're right. Let me ask you about something else."

fields.Title: Acele: ""Nothing," she says. "Anyway -- wha..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Nothing," she says. "Anyway -- what else?"

fields.Title: You: ""We'll see. I prefer to remain non-..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We'll see. I prefer to remain non-committal."
fields.Alternate1: "I spoke with the boys. Still undecided on the matter."

fields.Title: Acele: ""I know." She nods towards the slop..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I know." She nods towards the sloping mass of wood on the coast, then shivers. "It's not my idea. Andre and the boys found the place. It was supposed to be deserted, but now they can't even take it..."

fields.Title: Acele: ""Yeah, you know, that's what I mean..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, you know, that's what I meant -- Noid did. Noid put the padlock on the door."

fields.Title: Jump to: [Acele: ""What do you need to know?""]
Acele: ""Yeah, of course." She seems unsure..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, of course." She seems unsure of it, somehow.

fields.Title: Volition: "But not too long. This is important..."
fields.Dialogue Text: But not too long. This is important to her. She has the courage to ask.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""A crab *and* a banger?" The lieute..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "A crab *and* a banger?" The lieutenant raises an eyebrow.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Wonderful," the lieutenant says, s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wonderful," the lieutenant says, still looking at the ocean. "Revachol really needed another cop-for-hire. Maybe later we can go and get some doughnuts?"

fields.Title: Acele: ""Except that... yeah." She looks at..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Except that... yeah." She looks at the old wooden church up on the poles. As a mean wind comes bellowing in, the six-story structure lets out a doleful shriek.

fields.Title: Acele: ""Yeah, I guess you could say that.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, I guess you could say that."

fields.Title: You: ""Aha! The gardener was wrong -- I'm..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Aha! The gardener was wrong -- I'm not just some disco holdover, I'm going to experience the future."

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "She's less prone to blurting out 'c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She's less prone to blurting out 'crab-man!' than the others.

fields.Title: Acele: ""Hmm..." She sits back on the blank..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hmm..." She sits back on the blanket, ears red from cold. "That's odd. You should search her machine, maybe it says where she went?"

fields.Title: Acele: ""Oh, right. That's wise." She nods...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh, right. That's wise." She nods. "Take your time."

fields.Title: Empathy: "She doesn't get confused often, but..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She doesn't get confused often, but she is definitely confused now.

fields.Title: You: ""What would you stand to gain?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What would you stand to gain?"

fields.Title: You: ""We'll see. Go ahead and tell me.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "We'll see. Go ahead and tell me."

fields.Title: You: ""Okay then. About that church...""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay then. About that church..."

fields.Title: You: ""A crab *and* a banger?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "A crab *and* a banger?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant eyes you suspiciousl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant eyes you suspiciously.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I can see there's more to this sto..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I can see there's more to this story, detective," he says quietly. "But you're not the first corrupt cop in the RCM."

fields.Title: Acele: ""I know. I should have been able to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I know. I should have been able to control them. And I will in the future. I promise."

fields.Title: You: ""Electronic instruments -- like wha..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Electronic instruments -- like what?"

fields.Title: You: ""Why did this Noid-person put a pad..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Why did this Noid-person put a padlock on the church door?"
fields.Alternate1: "Why did Noid put a padlock on the church door?"

fields.Title: Acele: ""Good, so you believe me." She look..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good, so you believe me." She looks at the tent. "You should go tell this to Andre, he'll know what to do next."

fields.Title: You: ""I called it crime prevention. You'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I called it crime prevention. You'll have to go at it straight -- if you have it in you."

fields.Title: You: ""C'mon, quit stalling on me. What d..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "C'mon, quit stalling on me. What did he look like?"

fields.Title: Acele: ""You know, anodic, cathodic -- musi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You know, anodic, cathodic -- music that's made with electronic instruments."

fields.Title: You: ""Yes. Why do you ask?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes. Why do you ask?"

fields.Title: You: ""Okay, if *you personally* didn't,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, if *you personally* didn't, then who did?"

fields.Title: Acele: ""Wow! Thank you, that's... really c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wow! Thank you, that's... really cool of you." She clears her throat. "Anything else you want to know?"

fields.Title: Acele: ""Maybe you could *talk* to Andre an..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Maybe you could *talk* to Andre and the guys? Because there are some strange things going on in that church... if you're police you should look into it, right?"

fields.Title: You: ""I called it crime prevention. You'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I called it crime prevention. You'll have to go at it straight -- if you have it in you."

fields.Title: Drama: "C'mon. She obviously could. She alr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: C'mon. She obviously could. She already went into detail.

fields.Title: You: ""No. I'm *the police*.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "No. I'm *the police*."

fields.Title: Acele: ""What do you need to know?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What do you need to know?"
